<main>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Artifact Overview: SYLTrack (Mobile Application)</h2>
    <p>
      SYLTrack is a mobile application project focused on tracking user weight entries over time. The application supports adding,
      viewing, and managing weight data in a structured way and is designed to support consistency, usability, and maintainability.
      This artifact was originally created earlier in my program and was selected for CS 499 because it demonstrates my ability to
      design and engineer a complete software solution, including thoughtful user interaction, input validation, and organized code structure.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Category:</strong> Software Design and Engineering</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Why This Artifact Is Included</h2>
    <p>
      I included SYLTrack in my ePortfolio because it demonstrates professional software engineering skills beyond basic functionality.
      It reflects my ability to plan a solution, structure code for maintainability, and improve the application through enhancement work.
      This artifact also aligns with real-world development practices, including iterative improvement, testing/validation, and clear documentation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Software Design & Engineering Skills Demonstrated</h2>
    <div>
      <span class="badge">Object-Oriented Programming</span>
      <span class="badge">Maintainable Code Structure</span>
      <span class="badge">Input Validation</span>
      <span class="badge">UI/UX Improvement</span>
      <span class="badge">Documentation</span>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Design organization:</strong> improved structure to make the project easier to maintain and extend.</li>
      <li><strong>Reliability:</strong> strengthened validation to prevent invalid inputs and improve consistency.</li>
      <li><strong>Usability:</strong> refined user interactions and layout decisions to better support the end user.</li>
      <li><strong>Professional communication:</strong> documented changes and design choices for portfolio presentation.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Enhancement Summary</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Before:</strong> Core features worked, but the project needed improved structure and clearer presentation.</li>
      <li><strong>After:</strong> Enhanced the application to reflect stronger engineering practices, including cleaner structure and improved usability.</li>
      <li><strong>Result:</strong> A more professional, maintainable application that better represents software engineering skills.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Artifact Files & Documentation</h2>
    <p>
